-- Far East Former Director Acquitted of Fraud and Theft, RTHK Says
-- B y   W e n d y   M o c k
-- 2012-05-08T11:55:54Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-08/far-east-former-director-acquitted-of-fraud-and-theft-rthk-says.html
Far East Holdings International Ltd. (36) ’s
former managing director Duncan Chiu and two senior staff were
acquitted of fraud and theft charges,  Radio Television Hong Kong 
reported today.  Far East Holdings said in Sept. 2010 that one director and
two employees were charged by  Hong Kong  police’s Commercial
Crimes Bureau, without specifying the nature of the alleged
crimes or the names of those charged. Shares of the company have
been  suspended  since then.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Wendy Mock in Hong Kong at 
